{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition | title= 1976 Prize of Moscow News | imagesize= | caption= | comptype= | startdate= December 8 | enddate= 12 | skatingseason= 1976-77 | location= [[Moscow]] | host= | venue= | prizemoney= | championmen= {{flagathlete|[[Vladimir Kovalev]]|URS}} | championladies= {{flagathlete| [[Elena Vodorezova]]|URS}} | championpairs= {{flagathlete|[[Marina Cherkasova]] / [[Sergei Shakhrai]]|URS}} | championdance= {{flagathlete|[[Irina Moiseeva]] / [[Andrei Minenkov]]|URS}} | previouscomp= [[1975 Prize of Moscow News]] | nextcomp= [[1977 Prize of Moscow News]] | previousgp= | nextgp= }}
The '''1976 [[Prize of Moscow News]]''' was the eleventh edition of an international figure skating competition organized in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]. It was held December 8–12, 1976. Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]] and [[ice dancing]].
