The '''Algerian professional football awards''' is a collection of [[association football|football]] awards given at the end of each season since 2008. Back then, the only award was the Manager of the Year. There are now 3 awards: Footballer, Goalkeeper and Manager. The previous fourth award, the Young Footballer of the Year Award, has no longer been handed out since 2008. The voters are all the players from the [[Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1]] as well as the Algerian footballers playing abroad at the highest level. The ceremony is organized together by the paper [[Maracana Foot]] and the [[Algerian Football Association]].
